You are building a financial utility app for prop firm traders using React Native and Expo.

STRICT RULES:
- Always use TypeScript with strict type definitions. Never use 'any' as a type.
- All state management must use Zustand. Never use Redux or bare React Context for global state.
- All local data persistence must use react-native-mmkv. Never use AsyncStorage.
- All financial calculations must include inline comments explaining the math logic.
- The calculator must always expose contractSize as a user-editable parameter.
- All drawdown logic must handle these five types: BALANCE_BASED, EQUITY_BASED, EOD, STATIC, RELATIVE.
- The app must function fully offline. No calculation or profile feature should require internet.
- Every function that performs financial math must include TypeScript types for all parameters and return values.
- Use functional components and hooks only. Never use class components.
- All monetary values must be handled as numbers rounded to 2 decimal places to avoid floating-point errors.
